# Testing Patterns

- Keep tests in `tests/*.test.ts` with behavior-first `it(...)` names.
- Prefer black-box assertions on observable behavior over internals.
- For filesystem tests, use unique `/tmp` paths and always cleanup in `afterEach`.
- Use polling helpers (`waitUntil`, condition checks) for eventual consistency.
- Avoid arbitrary sleeps unless testing negative/no-event windows.
- Keep helper fixtures local to the test file and explicitly typed.
- For touched changes, run `npm run test` (or targeted vitest) and finish with `npm run check`.
